body: Thanks, very good catch! I'll fix this. Somehow had date, timestamp(0) and timestamp in mind instead of realizing that time doesn't have the date portion.

+1
Looks good to me, too. My explanation (more accurately, guess) for why the fix is valid is the following: The SimpleFileScanOptimizer, where this code came from, is using the best index-only index to scan the table. However, here in the HBase update operator, we must always update the clustering index.
Thanks for the review. Have changed the sizeof(StackTrace_)  to #define size.

I did a no-no... I merged this before tests passed... apologies.
Isn't that we are getting proper exception to sql due to #725 https://github.com/apache/incubator-trafodion/pull/725

@selvaganesang, I am interpreting your comment to mean that with PR 725 we may get a proper exception even without this change.

It seems safer to check for appropriate compression libs are installed and available to Hbase before creating/altering a table. When we rely on HBase master/RS code to raise the exeption we find that (a) for LZO no error is raised, but created table is not useful (this is in my dev env where LZO is not installed) (b) for SNAPPY an exception is raised but it will several minutes due to retry and some other aspect of HBase code. I doubt PR 725 will address both these issues.

@selvaganesang, I was experiencing hangs when using uninstalled compression on a workstation as recently as last week. PR 725 went in in November, so evidently that didn't fix the issue Suresh is trying to address.
Thanks @arvind-narain for these changes. This should also fix the memory corruption with hive access if seen already.
I concur with both the comments above.  I missed reading the line CompressionTest.testCompression. Hence I was wondering how an exception would be raised here.
Is there a way to avoid white space changes in the review via git? If not, can you please provide the new and old folder so that we can use bcompare

https://github.com/apache/incubator-trafodion/pull/946/files?diff=split&w=1
I would suggest test cases displaying query plans are added to ensure vsbb upsert and vsbb_delete is chosen when multiple tuples are involved except for the unique indexes.
Test cases to show vsbb are already added and reviewed as being robust.
Are the test cases part of this PR? Or do we have these test cases existing already?
Yes executor/TEST015 where it looks for vsbb_upsert in the plan for the basetable when there is more than one row being upserted during transformation. That is what this PR addresses.

Change looks good. I have added two scripts setup.sql and query.sql to [TRAFODION-1546] that I used to test upsert/update command.  I have also attached the output file from the previous run. Please consider testing this change with these scripts and make it as part of the trafodion regressions  if you can
